    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::random_id_c10). The expression can be simplified by factoring the numerator and the denominator. The numerator is a difference of squares, and the denominator is a perfect square trinomial. We have: \\begin{align*} \\frac{x^2 - 4}{x^2 + 4x + 4} &= \\frac{(x+2)(x-2)}{(x+2)(x+2)}\\\\ &= \\frac{x-2}{x+2}. \\end{align*}",
