    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::1e45287a). To add fractions, they must have a common denominator. The least common denominator of 2 and 4 is 4. We can rewrite $\\frac{1}{2}$ as $\\frac{2}{4}$. Therefore, $\\frac{1}{2} + \\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{2}{4} + \\frac{1}{4} = \\frac{3}{4}$.",
