    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::7d6c67e3). We can use a Venn diagram to solve this problem. Let the number of people who liked only apples be x. The number of people who liked only oranges is 50-20=30. The total number of people in the survey is x + 20 + 30 = 100. Solving for x, we get x = 50. Therefore, 50 people liked only apples.",
