    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::f65119c4). The cube root of 27 is 3, and the square root of 16 is 4. Therefore, $\\frac{\\sqrt[3]{27}}{\\sqrt{16}} = \\frac{3}{4}$.",
