    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::4c98f1a6). The area of a circle is given by the formula $A = \\pi r^2$, where $r$ is the radius of the circle. Substituting 5 for $r$ gives us $A = \\pi (5)^2 = 25\\pi$.",
