    correct: "-15",
    wrong: [["-9","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["3","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["11","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::837421b1). To find \\(f(-2)\\), we substitute -2 for x in the function: \\(f(-2) = 2(-2)^2 + 5(-2) - 3\\). Simplifying, we get \\(f(-2) = 2(4) - 10 - 3 = 8 - 10 - 3 = -5\\). Therefore, the value of \\(f(-2)\\) is -5.",
