    wrong: [["6","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["8","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["64","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::7a98f4e4). To solve for x, we substitute 48 for f(x) in the given equation, which yields 48 = 8√x. Dividing both sides of this equation by 8 yields 6 = √x. This can be rewritten as √x = 6. Squaring both sides of this equation yields x = 36. Therefore, the value of x for which f(x) = 48 is 36.",
