    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::34c8629c). To find the value of f(-2), we substitute -2 for x in the function f(x). This gives us f(-2) = 2(-2)^2 + 3(-2) - 5 = 8 - 6 - 5 = 3.",
