    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::4321657a). The sum of the roots of a quadratic equation in the form ax² + bx + c = 0 is given by -b/a. In this equation, a = 1, b = -2, and c = -8. Therefore, the sum of the solutions is -(-2)/1 = 2.",
