    chapter: "Advanced Math - Medium",
    title: "Advanced Math 88",
    prompt: "What is the value of the expression $\\frac{5^2 - 3^2}{2^2 - 1^2}$?",
    correct: "4",
    wrong: [["2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["8","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["16","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::67eb899b). We can simplify the expression using the difference of squares pattern: $\\frac{5^2 - 3^2}{2^2 - 1^2} = \\frac{(5+3)(5-3)}{(2+1)(2-1)} = \\frac{8 \\times 2}{3 \\times 1} = \\frac{16}{3} = \\boxed{4}$.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
