    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::f66432b2). A quadratic equation has exactly one solution if and only if its discriminant is equal to 0. The discriminant of the quadratic equation \\(ax^2 + bx + c = 0\\) is \\(b^2 - 4ac\\). In this case, the discriminant is \\(6^2 - 4 \\cdot 1 \\cdot k = 36 - 4k\\). Setting the discriminant equal to 0 gives \\(36 - 4k = 0\\). Solving for \\(k\\) gives \\(k = 9\\).",
