    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::76ab9e6b). Substituting $-2$ for $x$ into the equation for $f(x)$ gives us: $f(-2) = (-2)^3 + 2(-2) - 1$. Simplifying, we get: $f(-2) = -8 - 4 - 1$, or $f(-2) = -13$.",
