    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::234e3498). The circumference of a circle is given by the formula $C = 2 \\pi r$, where $r$ is the radius. Substituting 5 for $r$, we get $C = 2 \\pi (5) = 10 \\pi$.",
