    wrong: [["$\\pi$","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["$5\\pi$","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["$25\\pi$","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::42d8c34f). The circumference of a circle is given by the formula $C = 2\\pi r$, where $r$ is the radius. Substituting 5 for $r$ gives $C = 2\\pi(5) = 10\\pi$.",
