    wrong: [["-2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["1","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::b94a2009). The slope of a line passing through two points can be found using the formula: \\begin{align*}m &= \\frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1} \\\\ &= \\frac{-2 - 2}{3 - (-1)} \\\\ &= \\frac{-4}{4} \\\\ &= -1. \\end{align*} Therefore, the slope of the line is -1.",
