    wrong: [["1","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["10","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["20","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::78a213bf). The radius of a circle is half the length of the diameter. The length of the diameter can be found using the distance formula: $\\sqrt{(6 - (-4))^2 + (5 - 5)^2} = \\sqrt{10^2 + 0^2} = 10$. The radius is half this length, which is 5.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
