    wrong: [["25","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["50","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["200","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::9389fa32). The diameter of the circle is equal to the side length of the square. Since the radius of the circle is 5, the diameter is 10. The area of the square is then side length squared, or 10 * 10 = 100.",
