    title: "Advanced Math 162",
    prompt: "The function \\(f\\) is defined by \\(f(x) = \\frac{x^2 - 4}{x - 2}\\). For what value(s) of \\(x\\) is \\(f(x)\\) undefined?",
    correct: "2 only",
    wrong: [["-2 only","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["2 and -2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["The function is defined for all values of \\(x\\)","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::3e679962). A rational function is undefined when the denominator equals zero. The denominator of \\(f(x)\\) is \\(x-2\\), which equals zero when \\(x=2\\). Therefore, \\(f(x)\\) is undefined for \\(x=2\\) only.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
