    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::949c662a). Substituting $-2$ for $x$ in the function $f(x) = 3x^2 + 5x - 2$ yields $f(-2) = 3(-2)^2 + 5(-2) - 2$ = 12 - 10 - 2 = 8.",
