    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::34652f15). The circumference of a circle is given by the formula $C = 2\\pi r$, where $r$ is the radius of the circle. Substituting 5 for $r$, we get $C = 2\\pi(5) = 10\\pi$.",
