    wrong: [["30","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["60\\sqrt{3}","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["120\\sqrt{3}","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::e9ff8933). A regular hexagon can be divided into 6 equilateral triangles. The side length of each equilateral triangle is equal to the radius of the circle, which is 10. Thus, the perimeter of the hexagon is 6 * 10 = 60.",
