    wrong: [["0","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["1","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::f4a9fd2e). The expression on the left side of the equation is a perfect square trinomial: $(x + 1)^2$. Taking the square root of both sides, we get $x + 1 = 0$. Subtracting 1 from both sides gives us $x = -1$.",
