    wrong: [["-10","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["-2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["10","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::43417ac6). To find \\(f(-2)\\), we substitute -2 for x in the function: \\(f(-2) = 3(-2)^2 + 2\\). Simplifying, we get \\(f(-2) = 3(4) + 2\\), which equals 12 + 2, or 14.",
