    wrong: [["36","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["108","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["144","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::random_id_14). The circumference of the circle is $2\\pi r = 2\\pi(5) = 10\\pi$. Since the arc length is 10, the central angle represents \\frac{10}{10\\pi} = \\frac{1}{\\pi} of the circle. A full circle has 360 degrees, so the central angle measures $\\frac{1}{\\pi}(360)\\degree = \\frac{360}{\\pi}\\degree \\approx 114.6\\degree$. Of the answer choices, 72 degrees is closest to this value.",
