    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::8a4e419b). The sum of the solutions to a quadratic equation in the form $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$ is given by $-b/a$. In this case, the sum of the solutions is $-2/1 = -2$. Therefore, the sum of the solutions to the equation $x^2 + 2x - 15 = 0$ is -2.",
