    correct: "$11.25",
    wrong: [["$7.50","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["$9.75","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["$10.50","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::7c38d13a). The customer will spend 3 * $1.50 = $4.50 on apples and 5 * $0.75 = $3.75 on oranges. The total cost is $4.50 + $3.75 = $11.25.",
