    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::c7c7699b). The slope of a line passing through points $(x_1, y_1)$ and $(x_2, y_2)$ is given by the formula \\frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1}. Substituting the given points, we get \\frac{-4 - 5}{-1 - 2} = \\frac{-9}{-3} = 3. Therefore, the slope of the line is 3.",
