    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::84977e3c). If \\(x+2\\) is a factor of the polynomial \\(x^3+5x^2-4x-20\\), then by the Factor Theorem, the polynomial must equal 0 when \\(x=-2\\). Therefore, \\((-2)^3+5(-2)^2-4(-2)-20 = -8 + 20 + 8 - 20 = 0\\).",
