    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::9201b00f). The x-coordinate of the vertex of a parabola in the form $y = ax^2 + bx + c$ is given by the formula $x = \\frac{-b}{2a}$. In this case, $a = -1$ and $b = 4$, so the x-coordinate of the vertex is $x = \\frac{-4}{2(-1)} = 2$.",
