    wrong: [["-3 and 1","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["1 and -3","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["3 and -1","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::e60f8e2e). The equation is in the form of a quadratic equation, where the coefficients are 1, -2, and -3. This equation can be solved by factoring. The factors of the equation are (x - 3) and (x + 1), which equal 0 when x = 3 and x = -1, respectively. Therefore, the solutions are x = -1 and x = 3.",
