    wrong: [["-1","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["1","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::a214b1b9). First, factor the numerator: $\\frac{x^2 + 6x + 9}{x+3} = \\frac{(x+3)(x+3)}{x+3}$. Then, simplify by canceling out the common factor of $x+3$: $\\frac{(x+3)(x+3)}{x+3} = x+3$. Finally, substitute $x = 2$ into the expression: $2 + 3 = 5$.",
