    correct: "x = 1",
    wrong: [["x = -4","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["x = -1","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["x = 4","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::94831a0f). A vertical asymptote occurs where the denominator of a rational function equals zero, making the function undefined. The denominator of f(x) is (x - 1), and this equals zero when x = 1. Therefore, the function f(x) has a vertical asymptote at x = 1.",
