    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::f84948c7). Factoring the quadratic equation gives us (x - 4)(x + 2) = 0. Setting each factor equal to zero, we get x - 4 = 0 or x + 2 = 0. Solving for x in each equation gives us x = 4 or x = -2. Therefore, x = 4 is a solution to the equation.",
