    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::23987fc8). This expression is in the form of the difference of squares: (a + b)(a - b) = a^2 - b^2. In this case, a = \\sqrt{x} and b = \\sqrt{y}. Therefore, (\\sqrt{x} + \\sqrt{y})(\\sqrt{x} - \\sqrt{y}) = (\\sqrt{x})^2 - (\\sqrt{y})^2 = x - y.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
