    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::97c2f6f4). Triangle $ABC$ is a right triangle with base $AB = 6$ and height $BC = 4$. The area of a triangle is given by $(1/2)bh$, so the area of triangle $ABC$ is $(1/2)(6)(4) = 12$.",
