    wrong: [["5\\pi","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["25\\pi","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["50\\pi","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::random_id_55). The circumference of a circle is given by the formula C = 2\\pi r, where r is the radius of the circle. Substituting 5 for r, we get C = 2\\pi(5) = 10\\pi.",
