    wrong: [["2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["6","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["8","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::4d3672ba). The slope of a line passing through two points is given by the formula $\\frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1}$. Substituting the points $(2,5)$ and $(4,11)$ into the formula gives $\\frac{11-5}{4-2} = \\frac{6}{2} = 3$. Therefore, the slope of the line is 3.",
