    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::b7539c69). The given equation is a perfect square trinomial. It can be factored as $(x-3)^2 = 0$. Taking the square root of both sides gives $x-3 = 0$. Adding 3 to both sides, we get $x = 3$.",
