    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::74d55478). To factor the quadratic, we need to find two numbers that add up to -6 (the coefficient of the x term) and multiply to 8 (the constant term). These numbers are -2 and -4. Therefore, the factored form of the equation is $(x-2)(x-4) = 0$, and $a+b = 2+4 = 6$.",
