    correct: "5\\sqrt{3}",
    wrong: [["5","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["10","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["10\\sqrt{3}","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::83a1729c). Angle $AOB$ is a central angle of the circle, so triangle $AOB$ is an equilateral triangle. Therefore, chord $AB$ has the same length as the radius of the circle, 5. The height of triangle $AOB$ is $5\\sqrt{3}$, and this is also the length of the altitude from point $O$ to chord $AB$, which divides chord $AB$ into two congruent segments. Since the altitude bisects chord $AB$, the length of chord $AB$ is $2(5\\sqrt{3}) = 5\\sqrt{3}$.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
