    wrong: [["2","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["4","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["8","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::232e1e87). We can simplify the function first by factoring the numerator: $f(x) = \\frac{(x+2)(x-2)}{x-2}$. Since $x \\neq 2$, we can cancel the common factor of $x-2$, giving us $f(x) = x+2$. Therefore, $f(4) = 4 + 2 = 6$.",
