    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::28f4d38a). Substitute -2 for x in the expression for f(x): $f(-2) = 2(-2)^2 + 3(-2) - 1 = 2(4) - 6 - 1 = 8 - 6 - 1 = -9$.",
