    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::random_id_c11). We can solve this system of equations using elimination. Multiplying the second equation by 3, we get $3x-3y=3$. Adding this equation to the first equation, we get $5x=15$. Dividing both sides by 5, we find $x=3$.",
