    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::52f9a246). To find the median, we must first order the data set from least to greatest: 2, 2, 3, 4, 4, 4, 8, 8, 8, 13, 13. Since there are 11 data points (an odd number), the median is the middle value, which is 8.",
