    wrong: [["-5","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["5","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["6","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::4a1f5b7a). The sum of the solutions to the quadratic equation $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$ is given by $-b/a$. In this case, the sum of the solutions is $-6/1 = -6$.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
