    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::2466792a). We can factor the quadratic equation: $(x-1)(x-3)=0$. This tells us that the solutions to the equation are $x=1$ and $x=3$. The sum of these solutions is $1+3 = 4$.",
