    prompt: "When the astronaut was asked about the experience, he spoke about how he felt an overwhelming sense of awe. This feeling was so profound that he could only articulate it by saying, \"It's impossible to describe.\" The astronaut's experience, in essence, was too vast to be captured by language.\n\nWhich of the following choices best combines the two sentences at the underlined portion to maintain the meaning and structure of the passage?",
