    id: 321062,
    chapter: "Craft and Structure - Easy",
    title: "Craft and Structure 62",
    prompt: "The author uses a complex structure in this passage to guide the reader through the author's experience. The passage starts with a direct statement about the author's experience, then the author uses imagery to help the reader visualize the experience, and then the author ends with a direct statement about the importance of the author's experience. The use of imagery helps to make the passage more engaging and memorable. Which of the following techniques does the author use to make the passage more engaging and memorable?\n\nIn this passage, the author uses imagery to",
