    wrong: [["They knew that the data wouldn’t be clear until years after the experiment began, and they were confident in the overall methodology.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["The scientist knew that the data would not be clear until years after the experiment began, and they were confident in the overall methodology.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::197df82e). The underlined portion of the sentence should maintain consistency with the tense of the rest of the passage. Since the passage uses the past tense, the past tense form of \"would not be\" is the most appropriate choice.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
