    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::random_id_e9). The best way to combine the sentences is to use a comma and a coordinating conjunction to link the two independent clauses. The comma plus the coordinating conjunction \"and\" creates a grammatically correct and clear sentence. The other choices result in comma splices or other punctuation errors.",
