    title: "Expression of Ideas 81",
    prompt: "After a long day of exploring the bustling city, the tired travelers felt a sense of relief as they reached the tranquil countryside. The gentle breeze carried the scent of wildflowers, and the soft sounds of nature replaced the cacophony of city life. The quiet solitude provided a welcome respite from the constant stimulation of urban living. In this sense, the countryside offered a contrast to the city life the travelers had left behind.\n\nWhich choice best describes the overall structure of the passage?",
