    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::152d892d). The correct answer is A. In this sentence, the introductory phrase 'However, I was able to get a glimpse of the famous painting' is followed by a comma and then by the title of the painting, 'The Starry Night'. The title of the painting should not be set off by commas. This sentence does not require any commas. The other choices are incorrect because they all include commas that are not needed.",
