    chapter: "Craft and Structure - Medium",
    title: "Craft and Structure 183",
    prompt: "The author chooses to use the word \"perilous\" to describe the journey. The phrase \"perilous journey\" emphasizes the danger and uncertainty of the expedition, making the reader understand the risks the characters are facing. In the context of the passage, what is the effect of the author's choice of the word \"perilous\"?\n\nIn this passage, the word \"perilous\" is used to",
    correct: "emphasize the danger and uncertainty of the journey.",
    wrong: [["create a sense of wonder and excitement for the journey.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["highlight the importance of the characters' destination.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["suggest that the journey is a common and predictable one.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::random_id_english_8). The word \"perilous\" is used to emphasize the dangers and uncertainties of the journey, creating a sense of suspense and highlighting the risks involved.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
