    correct: "Because of the high-pitched sounds that flycatchers produce, they have developed an exceptional sense of hearing.",
    wrong: [["Because, of the high-pitched sounds that flycatchers produce they have developed an exceptional sense of hearing.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["Because of the high-pitched sounds that flycatchers produce; they have developed an exceptional sense of hearing.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["Because of the high-pitched sounds that flycatchers produce, they, have developed an exceptional sense of hearing.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::8942f3d8). The sentence contains a comma splice. A comma splice occurs when two independent clauses are joined together with only a comma. To correct the sentence, we can either use a semicolon, a period, or a conjunction. Choice B uses a comma followed by a coordinating conjunction, which corrects the comma splice.",
    source: 'OpenSAT',
