    chapter: "Information and Ideas - Hard",
    title: "Information and Ideas 582",
    prompt: "The study of genetics is the study of genes. Scientists have discovered that genes contain instructions for building and maintaining living organisms. These instructions are contained within the sequence of chemicals that make up a gene. Some of the most interesting discoveries in genetics have been about how genes change over time, and these changes often lead to the evolution of new species. What is the main idea of the text?\n\nThe main idea of the text is that",
