    wrong: [["The study’s findings have led researchers to believe: physical activity may have a positive effect on quality of life.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["The study’s findings have led researchers to believe that physical activity may have a positive effect; on quality of life.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["The study’s findings have led researchers to believe that physical activity may have a positive effect, on quality of life.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::e150a912). Choice A is the best answer because it combines the two sentences correctly without creating any punctuation errors. The other choices create punctuation errors; choice B uses a colon incorrectly, choice C uses a semicolon incorrectly, and choice D uses a comma incorrectly.",
