    chapter: "Craft and Structure - Medium",
    title: "Craft and Structure 734",
    prompt: "The author uses a number of devices to help the reader understand the complex ideas in the passage. For example, the author uses metaphors, similes, and analogies. The author also uses a variety of sentence structures to create a sense of rhythm and flow. What is the most likely reason why the author uses these devices?\n\nThe use of literary devices in this passage most likely helps to",
    correct: "make the passage more interesting and engaging.",
    wrong: [["create a sense of urgency and immediacy.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["explain the author’s personal beliefs and opinions.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."],["provide a clear and concise explanation of the topic.","This is one of the OpenSAT distractors, but it misses the specific evidence or calculation.","Use the passage, grammar rule, or math relationship named in the question rather than the closest-sounding option."]],
