    chapter: "Craft and Structure - Hard",
    title: "Craft and Structure 750",
    prompt: "The author uses a series of short, declarative sentences to describe the initial setting, which creates a sense of urgency and immediacy. This is in contrast to the longer, more descriptive sentences used later in the passage, which create a more contemplative and reflective tone. What is the effect of the author's use of short, declarative sentences in the beginning of the passage?\n\nThe author's use of short, declarative sentences in the beginning of the passage primarily serves to",
