    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::25e61f2c). Choice D is the best answer. Choice D uses the conjunction \"but\" to connect the two clauses, creating a complex sentence that maintains the original meaning. The other choices are incorrect because they either use incorrect punctuation or create a run-on sentence.",
