    lesson: "Source: OpenSAT (opensat::f81d448f). The speaker uses the phrase “it is a place for peace” to suggest that they find the countryside to be a place where they can find relief from the stresses of city life. This idea is further supported by the speaker’s description of the countryside as a “sweet” and “quiet” place.",
